titleInfo.title: CORTE DEL PALAZZO DVCALE DI VENETIA

relatedItem.note: It is useless to study costume without regard to the place in which it has been worn, yet how many costume books are there with innumerable examples of costumes without its necessarry architectural background. Costume is the fringe of Architecture. Vecellio seems to have realised this aud has placed several engravings to serve as backgrounds for his costume. The above cut is one of these
